'''Foursight Theatre''' is a female-led [[Devised theatre|devising theatre]] company, established in 1987 and based in the [[West Midlands (county)|West Midlands]] town of [[Wolverhampton]]. They are known for their tongue-in-cheek satire ''Thatcher The Musical!''<ref>{{cite news | title = Thatcher -- The Musical: Warwick Arts Centre, Coventry <!-- none twostar threestar fourstar fivestar --> - Reviews, Theatre & Dance - The Independent | accessdate = 2009-08-07 | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-dance/reviews/thatcher--the-musical-warwick-arts-centre-coventry--none-twostar-threestar-fourstar-fivestar-525703.html | location=London | first=Rhoda | last=Koenig | date=2006-02-10 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Romping with the Iron Lady - Telegraph | accessdate = 2009-08-07 | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/3650026/Romping-with-the-Iron-Lady.html | work=The Daily Telegraph | location=London | first=Dominic | last=Cavendish | date=2006-02-10 }}</ref> (produced in 2006 with the [[Warwick Arts Centre]]). They have also produced ''The Corner Shop'', about shopkeepers, customers and families, set in an abandoned shop in [[Sandwell]], [[West Bromwich]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Shelf life: the company that puts shopkeepers on stage. Brian Logan talks to Foursight Theatre | accessdate = 2009-08-07 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2008/oct/01/theatre.sitespecific.cornershop.bromwich | work=The Guardian | location=London | date=2008-10-01 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Daily Times - Leading News Resource of Pakistan - Do the cabinet shuffle...in ‘Thatcher: The Musical’ | accessdate = 2009-08-07 | url = http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2006%5C01%5C14%5Cstory_14-1-2006_pg9_6 }}</ref>
The company produces shows for national touring and site-specific work rooted in their home region.
