[[File:Fábrica de Arte Cubano stack (night).jpg|thumb|178x178px|Smokestack of La Fábrica de Arte Cubano illuminated at night]] '''La''' '''Fábrica de Arte Cubano''' (known locally as '''La Fábrica de Arte''' or '''F.A.C''') is an art gallery and club in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/travel/article/five-ways-to-experience-havana-cuba/index.html|title=The five best ways to experience Havana - CNN|date=2015-09-25|work=CNN Travel|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?q=Anthony+Bourdain+cuba&rlz=1C1GCEA_enUS759US759&oq=Anthony+Bourdain+cuba&aqs=chrome..69i57j0l5.5559j0j7&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8|title=Anthony Bourdain cuba - Google Search|website=www.google.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fac.cu/|title=Fábrica de Arte Cubano|website=www.fac.cu|language=es|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.lahabana.com/content/fabrica-de-arte-cubano-f-a-c/|title=Fábrica de Arte Cubano (F.A.C.) » LaHabana.com|date=2014-03-01|work=LaHabana.com|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref> The Fábrica's gallery and stage were established inside of a former [[cooking oil]] factory, and has since gained notoriety as one of Havana's premier nightclubs and art galas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://oncubamagazine.com/cultura/fabrica-de-arte-cubano-industria-de-creacion/|title=Fábrica de Arte Cubano: industria de creación - OnCuba|website=oncubamagazine.com|language=es-ES|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/havanas-new-place-to-be-in-a-factory-transformed/|title=Havana's new place to be - in a factory transformed|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en}}</ref> Several news outlets have described the factory as a symbol of Cuba's accelerating opening to the world.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2015/12/29/cubas-art-factory-aims-for-industrial-scale-hipness/|title=Cuba’s Art Factory aims for industrial-scale hipness|last=Miroff|first=Nick|date=2015-12-29|work=Washington Post|access-date=2017-09-19|last2=Voisin|first2=Sarah L.|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref> == History == The structure housing La Fábrica de Arte was built in 1910 as a cooking oil factory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.havanastreetview.com/directory/fabrica-arte-cubano-fac|title=Fábrica de Arte Cubano {{!}} Havana Streetview|website=www.havanastreetview.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://momvoyage.hilton.com/articles/best-things-to-do-in-havana-cuba/|title=12 Memorable Experiences in Havana, Cuba {{!}} Hilton Mom Voyage|date=2017-05-12|work=Hilton Mom Voyage|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brookings.edu/opinions/havana-bars-the-next-wave-of-private-innovation/|title=Havana Bars: The Next Wave Of Private Innovation|last=Feinberg|first=Richard E|date=|work=Brookings|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2008 a group of Cuban artists and musicians began to look for a centralized location in which art could be shown, leading to the group acquiring the closed factory in 2010. The current location opened in February 2014.<ref name=":1" /> It has been noted that the establishment attracts young Cubans and foreign nationals.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/nov/15/havana-fac-fabrica-de-arte-cubano|title=Ahmed Dickinson Cárdenas on Fábrica de Arte Cubano, Havana|date=2014-11-15|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-09-19|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref name=":1" />
