{{Infobox Podcast |width = |title = ''Monday Morning Podcast'' |image = Bill_Burr's_Monday_Morning_Podcast.jpg |caption = |hosting = [[Bill Burr]] |language = [[English language|English]] |rss = |atom = |updates = |length = Approx. 1-2 hours |camera = |direction = |production = |picture format = |video formats = |audio format = [[iTunes]], [[SoundCloud]], [[Google Podcasts]] |began = {{start date and age|2007|5}} |ended = |subjects = |genre = Comedy |provider = |url = [http://www.billburr.com/podcast billburr.com/podcast] }}
'''''Monday Morning Podcast''''' is a weekly comedy podcast hosted by comedian, actor and celebrity podcaster [[Bill Burr]]. It was independently recorded from May 2007 until October 2012, when it became a part of the [[All Things Comedy]] podcast network, which was founded by Burr and [[Al Madrigal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Monday Morning Podcast|url=http://allthingscomedy.com/channels/2/monday-morning-podcast|publisher=All Things Comedy|accessdate=16 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.detroitnews.com/story/entertainment/2015/10/21/everyman-bill-burrs-star-rises/74321604/|title=Everyman Bill Burr's star rises|last=Baetens|first=Melody|date=October 22, 2016|website=The Detroit News|publisher=|access-date=June 13, 2016}}</ref>
During each one-hour episode, Burr speaks without reservation and off-the-cuff about his past and recent experiences, current events, going on tour, sports, and offers advice to questions submitted by listeners. He is sometimes joined by his wife, Nia, and has many other featured guests and interviews with other comedians. The podcast is distributed through [[SoundCloud]], [[iTunes]], Google Podcasts, and [[CastBox]]. As of April 2017, the podcast has over 100,000 followers on SoundCloud and each podcast usually receives between 40,000 and 70,000 plays from that source.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/themonday-morning-podcast|title=theMonday Morning Podcast|website=SoundCloud|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> Statistics are not listed for iTunes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://allthingscomedy.com/about|title=The All Things Comedy Website}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.laweekly.com/arts/las-new-wave-of-indie-comedy-labels-4775121|title=L.A.'s New Wave of Indie Comedy Labels|last=Seabaugh|first=Julie|date=2014-07-03|website=L.A. Weekly|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref>
Beginning on March 12, 2015, Burr started releasing a second weekly edition, the ''Thursday Afternoon Monday Morning Podcast'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billburr.com/podcast/monday-morning-podcast-6-13-16|title=Monday Morning Podcast 6-13-16 - The Official Website of Bill Burr|date=2016-06-13|website=The Official Website of Bill Burr|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-13}}</ref> which he often refers to as the ''Thursday Afternoon Just-Before-Friday Monday Morning Podcast''. This podcast is formatted as a supplement to the regular weekly episode and features approximately half an hour of new material, followed by half an hour of clips from old episodes.
